cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.DC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with radio resource allocation in cellular networks. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper involves transmission overhead analysis and lower bounds of transmission overhead. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper discusses centralized and distributed architectures for resource allocation. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is relevant as the paper considers application usage variations. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is relevant as the paper compares distributed and centralized architectures.
